Thank you to the people of Owensboro, KY for your hospitality and warm welcome! You made this past weekend at the #owensboroairshow an absolute blast! Next stop: Chicago, IL, August 21-22, over the Chicago lakefront!

node.text:
What a great weekend in Michigan! @thunderovermichigan was a blast for the entire team, and we had an awesome time sharing the stage with @afthunderbirds! Thank you to everyone who came out and enjoyed the show! We’re back home in Pensacola, Florida after 3 weeks on the road gearing up for our next Air Show in Owensboro, Kentucky this weekend, August 14-15th. We hope to see you there!

#USNavy #USMC #AirShow #FlyNavy

node.text:
Thank you once again to the @fargoairsho! From it being our commanding officer Cmdr. Brian Kesselring’s hometown, to debuting our commemorative gold flight suits, it was a memorable weekend for the entire team. We can’t wait to see you again! 

Next up: Eielson Air Force Base for the Arctic Lightning Air Show!

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy

node.text:
Good Morning Fargo! We’re here in North Dakota for the @fargoairsho and this is a very special weekend for us! This is the hometown of our very own Cmdr. Brian Kesselring, commanding officer and flight leader of the Blue Angels! Cmdr. Kesselring graduated from Fargo South High School in 1995, and then went on to graduate from Concordia College in 2000. The entire team is honored to represent the Navy and Marine Corps in Cmdr. Kesselring’s hometown. Come out and see us this weekend July 24-25th at the Hector International Airport!

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy

node.title: Cmdr. Kesselring flies over his hometown!

Good Afternoon #BlueAngels fans! This past weekend was an incredible experience for our team. Being able to perform once again for the people of Pensacola Beach was amazing. Even with the rain, the best fans in the world came out to support! Thank you Pensacola Beach! Next stop, Fargo, North Dakota for the Fargo AirSho, July 24-25!

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy #Aviation

#USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy #Aviation #thunderonthebuffalowaterfront

node.title: CDR Ben Walborn Practice Flight over Buffalo Waterfront

node.text:
“Being a part of this Blue Angel family has been the greatest honor of my career. It has taught me the true meaning of teamwork and opened my eyes on what people can accomplish when they are all there to support each other.” - Aviation Structural Mechanic (Safety Equipment) Petty Officer 1st Class A.J. Acosta Jr., San Angelo, Texas

Acosta is a member of the Blue Angels’ Life Support department. The Life Support work center comprises Navy Aviation Structural Mechanics - Safety Equipment technicians and Aircrew Survival Equipment technicians. They maintain and repair the systems that support the life of the pilot in normal and emergency situations. These systems include air conditioning, avionics cooling, heating, canopy and ejection seat emergency escape systems, and more. They also maintain the personal flight gear the pilots must wear, such as helmets, oxygen masks, inflatable flotation devices, and ejection seat flight harnesses.

Additional photos are from Acosta's time serving with VFA 102 Diamondbacks.

@usnavy @marines #MaintainerMonday #USNavy #AirShow

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC #Airshows #Aviation #FlyNavy

node.text:
“I went to my first Blue Angels show at 2 weeks old, now I am a part of the same team..” 

-Aviation Structural Mechanic 1st Class Sam Smith, Virginia Beach, Virginia.

The Airframes work center is responsible for maintaining flight controls; hydraulic systems; landing, arresting and catapult gear; and performs composite and sheet metal structural repairs on the F/A-18 Super Hornet.

Additional photos are from Smith’s time as a SERE (Survival, Evasion, Resistance, and Escape) Instructor, and while serving with VFA 83 aboard USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN 69).

@usnavy @marines #maintainermonday #usnavy #airshow

node.text:
What a great weekend in Michigan! @thunderovermichigan was a blast for the entire team, and we had an awesome time sharing the stage with @afthunderbirds! Thank you to everyone who came out and enjoyed the show! We’re back home in Pensacola, Florida after 3 weeks on the road gearing up for our next Air Show in Owensboro, Kentucky this weekend, August 14-15th. We hope to see you there!

#USNavy #USMC #AirShow #FlyNavy

node.text:
“Being humble has always kept me hungry, striving for better opportunities and visibility within my community. Joining the Blues has provided me a scope to be seen and to impact my community and I absolutely love it here.” 

-Yeoman 1st Class Jessica Johnson, Sacramento, California.

Johnson is assigned to the events coordination office, and schedules preseason visits with show site sponsors and secures accommodations and ground support for each air show. Events personnel also create all air show schedules and coordinate team commitments, including the school and hospital visits, and manage the Blue Angels Key Influencer rider program.

@usnavy @marines #MaintainerMonday #USNavy #airshow
